  <!-- INTRO -->
  <section id="intro">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      The <strong>NATO 6T Battery</strong> is a globally standardized energy module designed
      for high-reliability use in military and defense vehicles. It combines robust construction
      with exceptional performance across extreme environments.
    </p>
    <p>
      Modern lithium-ion 6T systems deliver lighter weight, longer life, and higher power
      output compared to legacy lead-acid batteries — meeting next-generation battlefield and
      off-grid energy demands.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- TECH SPECS -->
  <section id="specs">
    <h2>Technical Specifications & Military Number</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard Designation:</strong> 6T / MIL-PRF-32143</li>
      <li><strong>Voltage:</strong> 24 V nominal (12 V variants exist)</li>
      <li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 100–180 Ah depending on chemistry</li>
      <li><strong>Chemistry:</strong> Li-ion (LFP / NCA) or Lead-Acid (AGM, Gel)</li>
      <li><strong>Dimensions:</strong> 269 × 256 × 230 mm</li>
      <li><strong>Operating Range:</strong> −46 °C to +71 °C</li>
      <li><strong>Pulse Discharge:</strong> up to 1100 A (30 s)</li>
      <li><strong>Cycle Life:</strong> 2000–4000 cycles</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

